text:
Wilson County (standard abbreviation: WL) is a county in the U.S. state of Kansas. In 2010, 9,409 people lived there. Its county seat is Fredonia.
19th century.
In 1855, Wilson County was created.
Geography.
The U.S. Census Bureau says that the county has a total area of. Of that, is land and (0.8%) is water.
Presidential elections.
Wilson County is very Republican. No Democratic Presidential candidate has won Wilson County since Franklin D. Roosevelt in 1932.
